<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-10-28T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-10-28T16:00:00-05:00" n="554" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d554">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">871.6363/239: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Riggs</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-10-28T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">October 28,
                                        1924—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>47. Suggestion in last sentence of your telegram 72 of October 21 is
                            approved. However, should a satisfactory solution not be reached within
                            a reasonable time the Department believes it might be advisable for you
                            to protest in accordance with its 41, September 26, 4 p.m.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>